&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fleet &amp;amp; Asset Operations Manager is a key member of the Business Operations organization and is responsible for all areas of fixed asset management, including fleet, capital equipment, and facilities. The Fleet &amp;amp; Asset Operations Manager is the primary driver of asset performance, fleet &amp;amp; asset strategy and standardization across brands, improvement efforts, issue resolution, risk mitigation, safety, cost management and on-going continuous improvement. They will support optimizing multimillion annual asset spend via data driven decision making and capital planning.&lt;/p&gt;
